<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 04:54 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7845 &Cx1f; tab-z
r k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-STINK-BOMBS-MILOSEVIC     05-07 1521
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STINK-BOMBS-MILOSEVIC-750&AMP;add-ECONOMIST-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STICKS'N'STONES MAY BREAK HIS BONES, BUT WORDS COULD REALLY HARM
HIM  
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Commentary Editors)   (This pithy, timely ``separate buy'' article is from the current
(week beginning 8 May 1999) Economist magazine.)  
  
 (EDITORS: We regret that this material is NOT available to clients
in Canada except to The Toronto Globe &AMP; Mail.)  
  
 (To publish this article, it must be purchased from the New York
