<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MCGREGOR-INTERVIEW-PHANTOM-MENACE-ADVISORY-NYTSF </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Bring on the lightsabers! &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Actor Ewan McGregor knows what he's getting into. As a star of
the year's most anticipated movie, ``Star Wars: The Phantom
Menace,'' he'll be the subject of fan frenzy. He'll be a media
magnet. He'll even be an action figure.
</P>
<P>
   And he's loving it!
</P>
<P>
   Find out what McGregor has to say about working with director
George Lucas and shooting ``The Phantom Menace'' in an interview
titled ``The Man Who Would Be Obi-Wan Kenobi,'' which is available
for purchase from The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   TAKE A LOOK ... the article can be found in your system under
the slug BC-EWAN-MCGREGOR-ON-PHANTOM-MENACE-ART-NYTSF. It has been
sent to category codes ``e'' and ``l.''
</P>
<P>
   This article is one of SIX that constitute The New York Times
Syndicate's STAR WARS COUNTDOWN package, which will guide your
readers to the May 19 premiere.
</P>
<P>
   THE PACKAGE INCLUDES INTERVIEWS WITH:
</P>
<P>
   _ Samuel L. Jackson, who plays Mace Windu
</P>
<P>
   _ Ewan McGregor, who plays Obi-Wan Kenobi
</P>
<P>
   _ Liam Neeson, who plays Kenobi's mentor, Qui-Gon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Rick McCallum, the producer of the film
</P>
<P>
   AS WELL AS FEATURES ON:
</P>
<P>
   _ The crazy antics of fans, from dressing up as ``Star Wars''
characters to creating wild Web sites. A fun piece that can easily
be localized.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Star Wars'' trivia (the ultimate quiz!)
</P>
<P>
   ---------ART IS AVAILABLE WITH EVERY STORY---------
</P>
<P>
   To purchase the McGregor interview or to get more details about
the STAR WARS COUNTDOWN PACKAGE, contact Sales Executive DEBRA
WEYDERT by phone, (732) 390-4480, or fa, (732) 390-4697.
</P>
<P>
   Thank you.
</P>
<P>
   _ The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
</TEXT>
