<P>
   TV-GREAT (Undated) _ There's one quality in Dickens that doesn't
travel easily to the 20th century: sentimentality. And that is one
quality PBS' ``Great Expectations'' wisely avoids. By Matthew
Gilbert. 700 words.
</P>
