 Friday, May 7, 1999   Editors:  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Newspapers that used the story slugged TEXAS-RANCH, which moved
Wednesday, May 5, on the Hearst News Service wire, may wish to run
the following correction:
</P>
<P>
   CARRIZO SPRINGS, Texas _ A story by the San Antonio Express-News
misidentified Charles Veldekens, who bought the Carrizo Springs
ranch owned by the Rev. Sun Myung Moon. Veldekens is the landlord
for the property occupied by the Doctors Hospital-Tidwell of
Houston and owns a small, limited-partnership interest. He is not
the chief executive of the hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
