<SLUG> BC-ZEDILLO-VISIT-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MEXICAN PRESIDENT TO VISIT CALIFORNIA 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SACRAMENTO, Calif. _ Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo will make
his first official visit to California May 18 to 20, Gov. Gray
Davis announced.
</P>
<P>
   Davis invited Zedillo to the state while the newly elected
governor visited Mexico City in February.
</P>
<P>
   Zedillo, who was elected in 1994, likely will travel to Los
Angeles, the Central Valley and to Sacramento, where he is expected
to address a joint session of the state Legislature.
</P>
<P>
   Details were being mapped out, but Davis has said Zedillo would
meet with California business leaders to promote trade.
</P>
<P>
   During his campaign, Davis, a Democrat, promised to usher in a
new era of warm cross-border relations with the state's southern
neighbor.
</P>
<P>
   Trade was at the heart of the governor's February mission to
Mexico City, and Davis said fostering a cooperative climate would
achieve that goal.
</P>
<P>
   Mexico surged past Japan to become the No. 1 importer of
California goods in the third quarter of 1998. The state shipped
$12 billion worth of goods to Mexico in 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
