<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 15:50 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8386 &Cx1f; taf-z
s f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-EXOTIC-CAR-WASH-ART-$     05-07 0455
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EXOTIC-CAR-WASH-ART-$ADV09-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IS THE WASH BRUSHLESS? YES, AND TOPLESS, TOO 
</HEADLINE>
   (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients. Non-subscribers
can make individual purchase by calling (888) 603-1036 or (888)
346-9867.)  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, MAY 9)  
 (af)  
 By DAN NEIL   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   GREENSBORO, N.C. _ In an economy as polymorphously diverse as
America's, it seems unlikely that Harper's II Exotic Car Wash is
the only one of its kind. But it could be. ``It's the only one I'm
aware of,'' said Eddie Collins, who owns both the car wash and a
nearby strip club.
</P>
<P>
   Seven year ago, Collins, who drives a blue Corvette convertible
and is partial to gold jewelry, was ``looking to make money during
the day'' at his club. He considered selling used cars or getting a
U-Haul franchise. Then the detailer who had worked on his own cars
quit. A neon light bulb came on over his head: Why not open a
topless car wash?
</P>
<P>
   City officals resisted at first, but Collins took steps to
preserve public decorum. A privacy fence eight feet high surrounds
the entrance to the metal building behind the club, where women in
G-strings wash the cars.
</P>
<P>
   Business has been brisk, he said, averaging 25 cars a day _ more
during the Greater Greensboro Open golf tournament or the ACC
basketball championships. The wash is open year-round; there are
heaters in the building for the comfort of workers, who do not
dress warmly.
</P>
<P>
   Washes are $15 a car, competitive with other hand washes in the
area. The workers receive only tips, plus what they make from table
and couch dances in the car wash area _ $10 and $20, respectively.
In a corner of the shed, ``V.I.P. areas'' are set aside for private
dancing.
</P>
<P>
   ``I like the hours,'' said Tammy, 24, who declined to give her
last name. ``It's more laid back, and you get tan.'' In the summer,
cars are often washed outdoors.
</P>
<P>
   Usually, the car washers do not work after hours at the club,
and vice versa. ``It's hard to find enough pretty girls who want to
do the work,'' Collins said. Sometimes, however, he will punish a
club dancer by sending her to the car wash _ ``especially those
prima donnas who think they are too good to wash cars.''
</P>
<P>
   And the cars do come clean, to the surprise of a first-time
customer. After he parked his green Saturn and took a seat nearby,
two attendants, Ariel and Tiara, untrussed themselves and began
hosing the car with warm water. They used lamb's-wool mitts to
lather up the car, raising the windshield wipers and paying close
attention to the wheels. After rinsing, they dried the car with a
hand chamois. Given that Ariel managed these feats in thigh-high
patent leather stilettos, a $5 tip did not seem extravagant.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
