keep an eye on high-crime venues. In Richardson, special lights
mounted on poles signal to the police that offenses _ namely
red-light runners _ have occurred. Running red lights has become
such a problem that for most of the past year, police agencies have
had special programs and units on the streets to combat it. By JIM
HENDERSON.
