wartime compensation, or charges of childhood sexual abuse, it has
rippled through boardrooms and bedrooms, emergency rooms and
courtrooms across the United States. Nearly everywhere, it seems,
except the university classroom. Many specialists say that American
universities have been slow to respond to the recent flood of
advances in the study and treatment of trauma. By Patricia Cohen.
