</P>
<P>
   COKE-LAWSUIT _ Coca-Cola Co. is expected to file its reponse to
an employee race discrimination case today. The Atlanta federal
court suit filed two weeks ago by four current or former
African-American employees alleges that Coca-Cola systematically
discriminates against blacks in pay, promotions, performance
evaluations and terminations. (Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DELL _ AUSTIN, Texas _ There were strategic reasons behind
Dell's plans for its first domestic plant oustide central Texas,
but in part, Nashville just felt like home. A day after the major
announcement, we look at the Austin area and the Nashville area,
and flush out more as to why Dell picked the Tennessee capital for
its 3,000-employee plant. (Mahoney, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   METRIX _ ATLANTA _Media Metrix Inc., which measures audiences of
Internet companies such as America OnLine Inc. doubled in its first
day of trading following an initial stock sale.
</P>
<P>
   The New York-based company rose 17 3/4 to 34 3/4 as about 1.9
million shares changed hands in late morning trading on the Nasdaq
Stock Market. Earlier, the shares touched 37. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HUDDLEHOUSE _ ATLANTA _ Huddle House is tired of playing the
poor cousin second fiddle? to other restaurant chains. The
Decatur-based company, which has spent the past 35 years catering
to blue-collar palates, is trying to expand its customer base with
a new look, expanded menu and slick television and prints ads.
(Poole, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
