<P>
   &UR; CONFLICT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA (Washington) _ Yugoslavia warms somewhat to a new
international peace plan, prompting a flurry of hopeful diplomatic
activity around the world despite warnings from both sides that the
details of peace remain largely unresolved. By Anne E. Kornblut.
1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA-UN (New York) _ Elbowed out of the Yugoslavia
conflict by Washington, the United Nations now has a big role to
play under a framework for peace. By Colum Lynch. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-WELCOME (Tirana, Albania) _ The welcome mat is getting
thin. Police are evicting Albanian refugees from hotels, others are
gouging their Kosovar cousins on apartments, tension is rising. By
Susan Milligan. 1250 words.
</P>
