undergraduate degree in business. On Saturday, he will don a cap
and gown and enter Sanford Stadium--where he has seen every Ga.
football game for decades--with the class of 1999, but his diploma
will show that the 89 year old Tucker was eligible for his
sheepskin in 1944. We visit Mr. Tucker (I hope on Wednesday
afternoon), who had a very successful life, and talk with him about
graduation. Ready for Saturday. (McCarthy, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).18. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
