<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Saturday, May 8, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   RAMIREZ-HOMECOMING (Los Angeles) _ After his ordeal in
Yugoslavian captivity, Andrew Ramirez came home to East L.A. to a
neighborhood that welcomed him as a hero. There was a flurry of
hugs and kisses. Cameras clicked away to catch him on the threshold
of his mother's house. By Troy Anderson. (Will move in ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   HOME-SHOOTING (Los Angeles) _ Three home-invasion robbers shot
and killed a record producer at his home studio after they tied up,
terrorized and robbed an aspiring vocalist who was auditioning.
Hillery Davis, a 52-year-old R&AMP;B and rap music producer, died about
8 p.m. after being shot in the chest by one of the assailants. By
Lisa Van Proyen and Philip Browne. (Will move in the ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TIPPER-VIOLENCE (Los Angeles) _ Students from Reseda and Eagle
Rock high schools will talk about school violence with Tipper Gore
at a UCLA town hall discussion on mental health. LAUSD officials
will also participate. Gore is convening several of these mental
health forums around the country to lead up to a big conference in
D.C. on June 7. By Mary Lou Aurelio. (Will move in the ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-BUDGET (Los Angeles) _ A special committee of the Los Angeles
City Council meets Friday to review the police and fire
departments' spending plans contained in the mayor's $4.2 billion
budget proposal for the fiscal year that begins July 1. By Rick
Orlov. (Will move in ``n'' California news file.
</P>
<P>
   LITTON-BID (Los Angeles) _ Litton Industries Inc.'s bid to
become the nation's biggest warship builder could encounter some
rough sailing. Not only does it have to past muster before two
corporate boards, the $2 billion offer faces scrutiny from federal
antitrust regulators, who recently blocked a bid by General
Dynamics Corp. to acquire one of the companies that Litton is
courting. By Greg Wilcox. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news
file.)
</P>
<P>
