<SLUG> BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, May 8. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
JENNY-ASSESS (Phoenix) - The suggestion to fix our culture in the
wake of the Littleton, Colo., killings is to teach media literacy
to our citizens. The idea: Had the cold-blooded killers understood
that TV shows and music and computer games aren't real _ had they
been intellectually equipped to passionlessly process the messages
they got from their entertainment choices _ perhaps there would now
be no grieving. Though it likely wouldn't have averted what
happened at Columbine High, media-literacy education for all is an
excellent idea. In the wake of Friday's verdict in ``The Jenny
Jones Show'' case, let's move right along to Lesson One. By DAVE
WALKER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
LEIBOWITZ-COLUMN (Phoenix) - There we were in mid-workout, each of
us on a Stairmaster. Well, actually, I was on the machine. Blondie
was on her cell phone. What followed was a hot debate on the
subject of cell-phone etiquette. Welcome to the new millenium,
where we, citizens who demand chitchat-free personal space, will
take back our restaurants, ballgames, produce aisles, theaters and
Stairmasters. By DAVID LEIBOWITZ. Story moved in the ``K''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BUFFALO-MUSEUM (Scottsdale, Ariz.) - Buffalo roam at Gemmie Baker's
insurance office. For more than 40 years, Baker has collected
buffalo memorabilia. You name it, he has it: ceramics, pelts, movie
posters, china, silver spoons, miniatures, taxidermy. Eight years
ago, Baker founded the Buffalo Museum of America in Scottsdale. His
insurance office takes up one corner of the first floor. The museum
sprawls across the rest of the two-story rented space. He says it's
the only place like it in the world. By BARBARA YOST. Story will
move in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
