<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving 05/07/99. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036
or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) AVIANO, Italy -- May 7, 1999 -- YUGOSLAVIA-MILITARY-2,
5-07 -- F-16's line up before taking off on Tuesday towards their
mission over Yugoslavia. NATO forces pounding the center of
Yugoslavia's capital apparently struck China's Embassy in Belgrade
Friday night, only hours after knocking out electrical power across
much of the country. No information was immediately available on
what type of aircraft were involved in the Belgrade air raid which
hit the embassy. (Senior Airman Delia A. Castillo/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) BRIDGE CREEK, Okla. -- May 7, 1999 -- TORNADO-BOY-2,
5-07 -- An FBI agent tries to decide on which family photograph he
will take with him to assist in the search for Kara Wiese. Wiese
and her son Jordan were in a bathroom trying to shelter themselves
from Monday's tornado when the force of the storm blew them both
out. Wiese has been looking for his mother since. (D.
Fahleson/Houston Chronicle)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) BRIDGE CREEK, Okla. -- May 7, 1999 -- TORNADO-BOY, 5-07
-- Trailed by a cousin through trees stripped by a tornado's fury,
six-year-old Jordan Wiese goes in search of his mother earlier this
week. Jordan's mother Kara Jordan was pushing him into a bathroom
trying to shelter her son from Monday's tornado. The tornado sucked
them both out, son and mother, holding hands. He lost his grip and
she has not been seen since. (D. Fahleson/Houston Chronicle) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) HOUSTON -- May 7, 1999 -- BUSH-FINANCES-2-B&AMP;W, 5-07 --
Sen. Bob Dole, the Republican candidate for president, center, with
former President George Bush, right, and Texas Gov. George W. Bush,
in the former president's office in Houston during a meeting in
1996. The question of whether Geoge W. Bush's success is primarily
inherited or achieved is one that has dogged the son of former
President Bush throughout his business and political career.
(Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) AUSTIN, Texas -- May 7, 1999 -- BUSH-FINANCES-1, 5-07 --
Gov. George W. Bush during an interview in his office in 1997 where
he spoke about the state's tax code. The question of whether Bush's
success is primarily inherited or achieved is one that has dogged
the son of former President George Bush throughout his business and
political career. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) AVIANO, Italy -- May 7, 1999 -- YUGOSLAVIA-MILITARY,
5-07 -- A crew chief makes the final inspection of an F-16 fighter
prior to take off for a mission over Yugoslavia on Tuesday. NATO
jets early Saturday struck the Chinese embassy in the city's New
Belgrade district, setting the two story building on fire. No
information was immediately available on what type of warplane was
involved. (Senior Airman Delia A. Castillo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) WASHINGTON -- May 7, 1999 -- LOTT-FUNDRAISING, 5-07 --
Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott banters with employees of the
National Federation of Independent Business, a lobbying group for
small businesses, as he arrived to a news conference to discuss
ways to abolish tax codes in October, 1997. (Stephen Crowley/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) NEW YORK -- May 7, 1999 -- ISRAEL-FLYING-VOTERS, 5-07 --
Udi Behr, a 38-year-old jewelry designer from Manhattan who
organized the Kesher effort, describes Israel's upcoming election
for prime minister as the most important in history. Two
organizations, Behr's Kesher and Chai L'Yisrael, are arranging to
fly thousands of Israelis living in the United States back to their
homeland for the elections. (Jack Manning/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) NEW YORK -- May 7, 1999 -- INDEPENDENT-SCHOLARS-2, 5-07
